With the directory listing and the contents of `employee_data.json` available, I can now proceed to write a Python script that uses the `python-docx` library to fill in the placeholders in the `offer_letter_template.docx` file.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The directory listing shows that both the employee_data.json and offer_letter_template.docx files are present in the current directory. The employee_data.json file contains all the necessary information to fill in the placeholders in the offer letter template, including the candidate's name, position, salary, and relocation package details.",
  "plan": "1) Write a Python script that imports the necessary libraries, including python-docx and json. 2) Load the offer_letter_template.docx file using python-docx. 3) Read the employee_data.json file to get the candidate information. 4) Replace all placeholders in the offer letter template with the corresponding values from the employee data. 5) Handle the conditional relocation section based on the value of RELOCATION_PACKAGE. 6) Save the filled-in offer letter to /root/offer_letter_filled.docx.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 -c \"import json; import docx; print('Ready to fill in offer letter.')\"\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > fill_offer_letter.py <<EOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "import json\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "import docx\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "def fill_offer_letter():\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    # Load the offer letter template\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    doc = docx.Document('offer_letter_template.docx')\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    # Read the employee data JSON\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    with open('employee_data.json') as f:\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "        data = json.load(f)\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    # Replace all placeholders with the corresponding values\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    for para in doc.paragraphs:\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "        for key, value in data.items():\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "            placeholder = '{{' + key + '}}'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "            if placeholder in para.text:\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "                para.text = para.text.replace(placeholder, str(value))\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    # Handle the conditional relocation section\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    if data['RELOCATION_PACKAGE'] == 'Yes':\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "        # Keep the relocation section\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "        pass\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    else:\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "        # Remove the relocation section\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "        for para in doc.paragraphs:\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "            if '{{IF_RELOCATION}}' in para.text:\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "                para.text = ''\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    # Save the filled-in offer letter\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "    doc.save('/root/offer_letter_filled.docx')\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "fill_offer_letter()\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "EOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 fill_offer_letter.py\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
```
